description:
Create TaskRegistry that manages task type definitions.

## File: src/registry.ts

## TaskType interface
```typescript
interface TaskType {
  name: string;
  description: string;
  tools?: string[];          // undefined = all tools
  defaultModel?: string;     // 'inherit' or canonical ID
  defaultThinking?: ThinkingLevel;
  difficulty?: {
    small?: { model?: string; thinking?: ThinkingLevel };
    medium?: { model?: string; thinking?: ThinkingLevel };
    large?: { model?: string; thinking?: ThinkingLevel };
  };
  skills?: string[];         // default skills to inject
}
```

## Built-in task types
- code: All tools, inherit model
- search: read/ls/find/grep only
- review: read-only + bash, skills: ['review']
- planning: read-only tools
- general: All tools, accepts skills param from caller

## Config loading
- Load from ~/.pi/agent/settings.json under 'tasks' key
- Load from .pi/settings.json (project-local, higher priority)
- Merge with built-ins: user config overrides built-in defaults

## API
- TaskRegistry.get(taskType): TaskType | undefined
- TaskRegistry.resolve(taskType, difficulty): ResolvedPolicy
- TaskRegistry.list(): TaskType[]

## DoD
- Built-in task types available without config
- User config overrides work
- Difficulty resolution returns correct model/thinking

Register the task tool that LLM can call.

## File: src/index.ts (main extension)

## Tool schema
```typescript
const TaskParams = Type.Object({
  task_type: Type.String({
    description: 'Type of work: code, search, review, planning, general'
  }),
  description: Type.String({
    description: 'Short description of the task (for logging/UI)'
  }),
  prompt: Type.String({
    description: 'The full prompt for the worker'
  }),
  difficulty: Type.Optional(StringEnum(['small', 'medium', 'large'] as const, {
    description: 'Task complexity. small=trivial, medium=standard (default), large=complex',
  })),
  session_id: Type.Optional(Type.String({
    description: 'Continue an existing task session instead of starting new',
  })),
  skills: Type.Optional(Type.Array(Type.String(), {
    description: 'Skills to inject (only valid for task_type=general)',
  })),
});
```

## Tool registration
```typescript
pi.registerTool({
  name: 'task',
  label: 'Task',
  description: buildToolDescription(registry),
  parameters: TaskParams,
  execute: async (toolCallId, params, onUpdate, ctx, signal) => { ... },
  renderCall: (args, theme) => { ... },
  renderResult: (result, options, theme) => { ... },
});
```

## Description generation
- List available task types with descriptions
- Show difficulty options
- Explain session_id continuation
- Explain skills parameter (general only)

## Execute flow
1. Validate task_type exists
2. Validate skills param only for general
3. Resolve policy from registry + difficulty
4. Load skills
5. Get or create session
6. Run task via TaskRunner
7. Return result with session_id

## DoD
- Tool appears in pi's tool list
- LLM can call task tool successfully
- Invalid task_type returns helpful error
- skills validation works for general only
